article.headline: Langley's late OT bucket send UNC Greensboro past Eastern Kentucky 87-85

images.name: Kobe Langley wins it for UNCG at the buzzer with left-handed floater
images.caption: Kobe Langley hits the floater as the buzzer sounds to lift UNC-Greensboro over Eastern Kentucky in overtime.

article.linkText: Langley's late OT bucket send UNC Greensboro past Eastern Kentucky 87-85
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Kobe Langley scored 19 points and his left-handed floater off a drive in the lane with less than a second left carried UNC Greensboro past Eastern Kentucky 87-85 in overtime Thursday night. Donovan Atwell led the Spartans (7-1) with 24 points shooting 8 for 12 shooting including 8 for 10 from 3-point range. Mikeal Brown-Jones scored 19 points and Langley finished 8-for-11 shooting. UNC Greensboro now has won six straight. Devontae Blanton led the way for the Colonels (3-4, Atlantic Sun Conference) with 22 points, eight rebounds, six assists and three steals. Leland Walker added 18 points and Isaiah Cozart scored 16 points. UNC Greensboro hosts Elon on Sunday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
